                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33292",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The reason of this segfault seem to be the huge memory footprint used when initiating date objects.\n\nSome performance increasements have been implemented which prevent that this error occurs in this place.\n\nStill, ZF is not able to solve a PHP internal error. The given code should have worked even with the used memory.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-07T11:48:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-07T11:48:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33294",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexadriaanse",
                        "name": "alexadriaanse",
                        "displayName": "Alex Adriaanse",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Understood.  But wouldn't it be cleaner to move the string cast up a few lines anyway?  The workaround seems easy and clean.",
